Concept.displayName: pT0: No evidence of primary tumor
pT1: Tumor confined to nasopharynx, or tumor extends to oropharynx and/or nasal cavity without parapharyngeal extension#
pT3: Tumor invades bony structures of skull base and/or paranasal sinuses
pT4: Tumor with intracranial extension and/or involvement of cranial nerves, hypopharynx, orbit, or with extension to the infratemporal fossa/masticator space
